genresAdvancedInfo.name: ruta destroy
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Ruta Destroy is a subgenre of punk rock that emerged in Spain in the late 1970s. It is known for its aggressive, fast-paced sound and politically charged lyrics that often address social issues such as poverty, unemployment, and government corruption. The name "Ruta Destroy" comes from the fact that many of the bands associated with the genre played in bars and clubs along a particular route in Madrid.
